# Tailwind

- Use Tailwind CSS in JSX; avoid large one-off `<style>` blocks unless necessary—prefer utilities and `src/styles.css` theme tokens.
- Do **not** use `space-y-*` or `space-x-*`; use flex or grid with `gap-*` instead.
- Avoid arbitrary values when an existing utility class is close to the desired value.
- Use the **semantic color system** in `src/styles.css` (`@theme`, `light-dark(...)`, CSS variables such as `--color-surface`, `--color-text`, etc.).
- Do **not** introduce new colors that break the existing light/dark semantic system—extend `styles.css` coherently if new tokens are required.
- Reuse existing component patterns in `src/components/song-mode/` for buttons, cards, and chrome instead of inventing divergent styles.
- Follow the shared cursor convention in `src/styles/base.css`: clickable controls should inherit pointer from semantic elements (`button`, `a`, TanStack `Link`) or from `[role="button"]` when non-semantic structure is required.
- Prefer semantic interactive elements first; if a non-semantic wrapper must be clickable, it must include `role="button"` (with keyboard support) so cursor and accessibility behavior stay consistent.
